others, and if I deliver up my
body *to be burned, but do
not have love, I receive no
benefit.
4 Love is patient and kind.
Love does not envy or boast.
It is not puffed up 5 or
rude. It does not seek its
own way, it is not irritable,
and it keeps no record of
wrongs. 6 It does not re-
joice over unrighteousness,
but rejoices with the truth.
7 It bears all things, believes
all things, hopes all things,
and endures all things.
8 Love never fails.
But
as for prophecies, they will
come to an end; as for
tongues, they will cease; as
