GALATIANS
Greeting
Paul,
an apostle—
appointed not by men nor
through man, but by Jesus
Christ and God the Father,
who raised him from the
dead— 2 and all the brothers
with me, to the churches of
Galatia: 3 Grace to you and
peace from God *the Father
and our Lord Jesus Christ,
4 who gave himself for our
sins to deliver us from the
present evil age, according
to the will of our God and
Father. 5 To him be the glory
forever and ever. Amen.
