once been enlightened, who
have tasted the heavenly
gift, who have shared in
the Holy Spirit, 5 who have
tasted the good word of
God and the powers of
the coming age, 6 and yet
have fallen away, since, to
their own harm, they are
crucifying the Son of God
all over again and exposing
him to public shame. 7 For
land that has drunk the
rain that often falls upon
it, and produces a crop
useful to those for whom
it is cultivated, receives a
blessing from God. 8 But
land that bears thorns and
thistles is worthless and on
the verge of being cursed; its
end is to be burned.
9 Even though we speak
in this way, beloved, we are
confident of better things in
your case, things that per-
tain to salvation. 10 For God
is not unjust; he will not
forget your work and the
*labor of love that you have
shown toward his name by
serving the saints, as you
still do. 11 We want each
one of you to show the same
earnestness to have the full
assurance of hope to the
very end, 12 so that you will
not be sluggish, but imita-
