also blessed Abraham, who
had received the promises.
7 It is beyond all dispute
that the inferior is blessed
by the superior. 8 In the
one case, tithes are received
by mortal men, but in the
other case, they are received
by one who is attested to
be living. 9 One might even
say that Levi himself, who
receives tithes, paid tithes
through Abraham. 10 For
Levi was still in the loins of
his ancestor Abraham when
Melchizedek met him.
